name: raptor-necropsy-data-from-the-moon-lake-electric-company-service-area-utah-and-colorado-20-2004
notes: The data are the results of clinical necropsies of raptors and ravens done in cooperation with pathologists at the Veterinary Teaching Hospital and Diagnostics Laboratory, Colorado State University, Fort Collins. Dead birds were recovered along electric distribution lines throughout the service area of the Moon Lake Electrical Association, northeastern Utah and northwestern Colorado. Data were collected between June 2001 and December 2004.
